            "title": "The tail plays a major role in the differing manoeuvrability of two sibling species of mouse-eared bats (Myotis myotis and Myotis blythii)",
            "creators": [
                {
                    "creatorType": "author",
                    "firstName": "Daniela A.",
                    "lastName": "Schmieder"
                },
